      "writtenOn": "2017-11-02T19:23:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We haven’t invented a mapping of non-Windows bits to the format that’s used in minidumps for the memory map. We haven’t implemented MemoryMap() on macOS yet either.\n\nWe should eventually do this (and implement it on macOS), but I don’t think that you need to focus on it until after we have the initial Chromium integration done, unless it naturally falls out of other work.\n\nhttps://crashpad.chromium.org/bug/20.",
      "revId": "780b4950ed1b7cec5e31246499a42e04d1665077",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
